						               													<description>Horseplay was originally designed in the 1980s, then published online in 2014.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses a square 9x9 grid as a playing area. Players begin in the middle of one side of the board, called the &amp;quot;paddock.&amp;quot; Letter tiles are placed on alternating tiles on the grid, with empty spaces between each tile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players then use chess-style movement to collect the letter tiles before ending the round in a designated corner of the board. Once a player lands in a corner square, the &amp;quot;stables,&amp;quot; their play is ended and they must wait for other players to finish.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game, the players spell a word with the tiles they have collected. The highest scoring tile wins. Players who did not end in a &amp;quot;stable&amp;quot; get no points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
